cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 

1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses an RF sensor network and its ability to monitor RSS values on links in the network. This falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 

2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper provides a statistical model for the RSS variance as a function of the person's position w.r.t. the transmitter and receiver. This involves the use of information theory concepts to analyze the data. 

3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses device-free localization, i.e., locating a person or object moving in the area in which the network is deployed. This involves the use of control systems to track the movement of the person or object. 

4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the spatial characteristics of the RF sensor network and how it can be used to locate a person or object. This involves the use of multimedia technologies to visualize the data. 

5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper discusses the use of an RF sensor network to monitor the movement of people or objects in a given area. This has implications for security and privacy, which falls under the domain of cryptography and security.
